ANALYSIS
--------
Both failures are the same underlying issue: Agency's typechecker does not
recognize `.length` as a valid property on `string` types. This is a
typechecker limitation/bug -- `.length` is a standard property on strings in
JavaScript/TypeScript and should be supported.

The code itself is correct and would work at runtime since Agency compiles to
TypeScript where `string.length` is valid.

These two files are excluded from the typechecker fixture integration test
(lib/typeChecker/fixtureTypeCheck.integration.test.ts) via the SKIP_TYPECHECK
set until the typechecker is updated to support string.length.
